      <h3>Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Options give you the right but not the obligation to buy/sell.</li>
        <li>Calls are used when expecting price increase; puts when expecting a decrease.</li>
        <li>Strike price, premium, and expiration are core terms to know.</li>
        <li>Options can be used for hedging or speculation.</li>
        <li>Always manage your risk — know your max loss before entering a trade.</li>
